

'''Book: Cory Doctorow. Little Brother.'''


=Description=

Pat Kane:

"Doctorow's America is essentially the Bush-Cheney-Rumsfeld regime, after the Next Big Attack. Their panoptical paranoia provides him with many opportunities to show the ingenuity of the digital hipster who says "yes we can" to any subversive opportunity computers, software and networks can bring. For Doctorow, "little brother" means [[Sousveillance]] versus surveillance – the eternal vigilance of the [[Netizen]] in defense of the principles of their Republic."
(http://theplayethic.typepad.com/play_journal/2008/11/little-brothers-in-the-digital-panopticon.html)

Full review by Pat Kane at http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/reviews/remixby-lawrence-lessigbr-little-brother-by-cory-doctorow-1037787.html



